body:
### Description
On some android devices the circles are drawn on the screen visibly lengthened. To obtain a visibly acceptable circle you must draw an oval with a ratio of 10 to 8, then with rx=100 pixels and ry=80 pixels.

### Code
           var info =  e.Info;
           var surface = e.Surface;
           var canvas  = surface.Canvas;

            // CLEARING THE SURFACE
            canvas.Clear(SKColors.White);


            // DRAWING SHAPES

            // create the paint for the outline of the circle
            SKPaint paint = new SKPaint
            {
                Style = SKPaintStyle.Stroke,
                Color = SKColors.Red,
                StrokeWidth = 25
            };

            // draw the outline of the circle
            canvas.DrawCircle(info.Width / 2, info.Height / 2, 100, paint);

### Expected Behavior
I expect a circle with the same height and width.

### Actual Behavior
On some Android devices the circle shown on the display is extended vertically.

### Basic Information

- Version with issue:  1.60.0
- IDE:  Visual Studio Community 2017 (15.6.7)
- Platform Target Frameworks: 
  - Android: 6.0
 
### Screenshoot
![img_4185b](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/36405345/39711381-e40192cc-521f-11e8-91cc-8bf56f1509cd.jpeg)
